Officer Jingleberry,

I know this is going to sound absolutely crazy, but I've been documenting some really strange activity around the neighborhood and I think you need to know about it.

For the past week, I've been seeing small figures moving around at night. At first I thought it was just my imagination, or maybe kids playing pranks, but I've been keeping a log:

DECEMBER 12th - 2:30 AM: Saw tiny lights moving in Old Pete's garden. Heard what sounded like miniature construction work.

DECEMBER 14th - 3:15 AM: Watched small shapes carrying what looked like electronics parts from house to house. They were wearing pointed hats!

DECEMBER 16th - 1:45 AM: Actually saw them! Those old "Gnomes in Your Home" decorations that were WALKING! I could clearly see their distinctive candy cane striped legs moving around! They were taking things from Sparky's workshop and loading them into tiny carts.

DECEMBER 17th - 4:00 AM: They were at Granny Crumbleton's house, stealing cooling racks and... wait, this is where it gets really weird... they were measuring her refrigerator with tiny rulers!

I know how this sounds. I know you probably think I've been hitting the eggnog too hard this holiday season, but I swear this is real. I even tried to take pictures, but they always seem to know when I'm watching and disappear.

The thing is, I think they're building something. All the items they're taking - electronics, cooling components, small tools - it's like they're working on some kind of project. And I think it has something to do with 

